<para>
  The Heat Equation is
  <equation id="Eqn-Heat">
    <alt role="tex">
      \[ C\frac{\partial T}{\partial t} + \nabla\cdot{\bf J} = \dot Q \]
    </alt>
  </equation>
  where <inlineequation><alt role="tex">\(T\)</alt></inlineequation>
  is the <xref linkend="Field-Temperature"/> &field;,
  <inlineequation><alt role="tex">\(C\)</alt></inlineequation> is the
  <link linkend="PropertyType-HeatCapacity">heat capacity</link>,
  <inlineequation><alt role="tex">\(\bf J\)</alt></inlineequation> is
  the <link linkend="Flux-Heat_Flux">heat flux</link> and
  <inlineequation><alt role="tex">\(\dot Q\)</alt></inlineequation> is
  a <link linkend="PropertyType-HeatSource">heat source</link>.
</para>



